    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-05T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-05T12:00:00-05:00" n="354"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.3394/265: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-05T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 5, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>139. Reference, your 221, July 22, 5 p.m., and previous.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>For your information. Commander-in-Chief<note n="48" xml:id="d354fn48"
                            >Admiral Harry E. Yarnell, Commander in Chief, U. S. Asiatic Fleet, at
                            Shanghai.</note> recommends through the Navy Department that in view of
                        the situation in Far East this Department notify Japanese Government that
                        proposed visit of the Commander-in-Chief to Japan be indefinitely postponed.
                        Both Departments approve.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Please appropriately inform Foreign Office that visit will be indefinitely
                        postponed.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
